-- Dairibord of Zimbabwe Says Annual Profit Rises 15%
-- B y   G o d f r e y   M a r a w a n y i k a   a n d   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-02-29T16:26:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-29/dairibord-of-zimbabwe-says-annual-profit-rises-15-.html
Dairibord Holdings Ltd (DZLH) ., a
Zimbabwean dairy company, said annual profit rose 15 percent.  Net income in the year ended Dec. 31 rose to $7.1 million
from $6.2 million the year earlier, Group Chief Executive
Officer Anthony Mandiwanza said at a presentation in Harare, the
capital, today. Revenue rose 28 percent to $95.9 million and is
forecast to jump a further 23 percent this year, said
Mandiwanza.  The company declared a dividend of 0.44 of a cent, he said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Godfrey Marawanyika in Johannesburg at 
